Method Detail

parse

List parse()
           throws IOException,
                  ParseException
Parse the file and return a List of AnalyzedItem's.

Returns:
a List of AnalyzedItem's
Throws:
IOException - is thrown for file Input/Output errors
ParseException - is thrown for parse errors
See Also:
AnalyzedItem

clear

void clear()
Clear the file parser so that the parse() method can be called again if needed.

dispose

void dispose()
Dispose of resources being used. The file parser will be invalid after this method is called and must not be reused, so a new file parser must be instantiated.
